The United States and Angola are celebrating 30 years of diplomatic relations and recommitting to achieving a shared vision of a more peaceful, secure, and democratic world. The two countries are working together to address global challenges such as climate change and promote cooperation across the Atlantic region. They are also expanding economic cooperation, including pursuing investments in sustainable infrastructure to connect Angola to global markets. The United States will continue to support Angola in promoting peace, stability, democratic institutions, combating corruption, and fostering inclusivity in the political process.